</p>
<p>And since <em>this</em> process will be the same as upgrading, we can re-use this exactly.
Just change <code>otherPlan</code> to <code>otherDurationPlan</code>... in all 4 places. Update the text
to "Bill" and then <code>otherDurationPlan.duration</code>. So, this will say something like
"Bill yearly".</p>
<h2 id="dump-the-upcoming-invoice">Dump the Upcoming Invoice <a class="headerlink" href="monthly-to-yearly#dump-the-upcoming-invoice" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Before we try this, go back into <code>ProfileController</code> and find <code>previewPlanChangeAction()</code>.
The truth is, changing a plan from monthly to yearly should be <em>identical</em> to upgrading
a plan. But, it's not <em>quite</em> the same. To help us debug an issue we're about to
see, dump the <code>$stripeInvoice</code> variable:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="66fcd20e47">
